      "updated": 1784736534650,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "The problem just gives up an array of arrays, now those array inside have only ever 2 elements, those element now corresponds to the start and end indices of an array. effectively making\nthose arrays intervals of an array now our job is to find overlapping intervals and merge them all if an interval cannot be merged with any we still keep them. the new array of this simplified \nmerged intervals is what we then return. so we are again returning an array of arrays in the end right.",
      "fontSize": 124,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "The problem just gives up an array of arrays, now those array inside have only ever 2 elements, those element now corresponds to the start and end indices of an array. effectively making\nthose arrays intervals of an array now our job is to find overlapping intervals and merge them all if an interval cannot be merged with any we still keep them. the new array of this simplified \nmerged intervals is what we then return. so we are again returning an array of arrays in the end right.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "4I6DoaW4wFkeWI2ssqmek",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 5794.49706316407,
      "y": -5746.629347500861,
      "width": 21766.958984375,
      "height": 620,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#c2255c",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 2,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b3R",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1480856452,
      "version": 1553,
      "versionNonce": 2012959926,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1784743856263,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. i though about the interval sizes, though about a maintaining a minimum and maximum when going ahead and merging rules etc. while i couldn't find any truly optimal approach i just found one way to atleast do this thing in a single pass with an extra space of n\nwhere n is the number of arrays in the enclosing array. i mean i will still have like an array of arrays as the answer with each array inside the array, containing just two numbers always. the time complexity of my solution is O(n^2) because i do a single pass over the outer the outer array and storing aother array the min and max encountered\nnow if the for the current array inside the input i find the min and max to not be in range of any of the arrays insdie the extra n space array i created that means its just own interval and i should add it in the n array if it overlaps with any of the intervals inside this n array i edit our the n array  entry with the correct new proper merged interval\nwhen i am done iterating over the element either it will be in this n array and successfully merge with it's entry or just become another separate entry inside this n array resulting in a successfully merged n array out of the input. i am 100% super sure this is quite a lame approach but let's code this one and then look at the elegance of the solution shall we. ",
      "fontSize": 124,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. i though about the interval sizes, though about a maintaining a minimum and maximum when going ahead and merging rules etc. while i couldn't find any truly optimal approach i just found one way to atleast do this thing in a single pass with an extra space of n\nwhere n is the number of arrays in the enclosing array. i mean i will still have like an array of arrays as the answer with each array inside the array, containing just two numbers always. the time complexity of my solution is O(n^2) because i do a single pass over the outer the outer array and storing aother array the min and max encountered\nnow if the for the current array inside the input i find the min and max to not be in range of any of the arrays insdie the extra n space array i created that means its just own interval and i should add it in the n array if it overlaps with any of the intervals inside this n array i edit our the n array  entry with the correct new proper merged interval\nwhen i am done iterating over the element either it will be in this n array and successfully merge with it's entry or just become another separate entry inside this n array resulting in a successfully merged n array out of the input. i am 100% super sure this is quite a lame approach but let's code this one and then look at the elegance of the solution shall we. ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
